  "prompt": "Can I get iPhone replaced from Apple Store if it is covered under warranty?",
  "response": "Yes, if your iPhone is covered under warranty, you can get it replaced at an Apple Store. The device will be examined to determine if the issue is covered under the warranty. If it is, Apple will typically offer to repair your iPhone or provide a replacement. It's a good idea to make an appointment at the Genius Bar beforehand to avoid long waiting times. Additionally, remember to back up your data before going to the Apple Store, as replacement procedures may involve erasing the device's data.",
